## Diagram DSL Conformance

The auto-generated diagram will follow this structure:

```
digraph notion_obsidian_viewer {
  graph [goal="Create elegant web viewer combining Obsidian + Notion" rankdir=LR]

  start [shape=Mdiamond label="START"]
  done [shape=Msquare label="DONE"]

  // Ideas lane (11 cards) - box shape
  idea_slash_commands [shape=box prompt="Implement Notion's signature '/' command..."]
  idea_tag_browser [shape=box prompt="Create dedicated tag browser view..."]
  idea_team_sharing [shape=box prompt="Since this will be used by teams..."]
  // ... 8 more idea cards

  // Plan lane (17 cards) - box shape with more detail
  plan_sqlite_backend [shape=box prompt="Implement SQLite database to store..."]
  task_sqlite_schema [shape=box prompt="Create database schema to store: Note content..."]
  task_markdown_parser [shape=box prompt="Implement or integrate markdown parser..."]
  // ... 15 more plan/task cards

  // Spec lane (6 cards) - box shape with goal_gate=true
  spec_mock_sync [shape=box goal_gate=true prompt="Create mock implementation..."]
  spec_frontend_first [shape=box goal_gate=true prompt="Development should prioritize..."]
  spec_quick_search [shape=box goal_gate=true prompt="Implement keyboard-activated search..."]
  // ... 3 more spec cards

  // Flow edges
  start -> idea_slash_commands
  idea_slash_commands -> plan_sqlite_backend [condition="prioritized"]
  plan_sqlite_backend -> spec_quick_search [condition="approved"]
  spec_quick_search -> done [condition="implemented"]
}
```

**Note**: No diamond decision nodes or hexagon human-wait nodes are currently defined in cards. These would need to be explicitly created as cards with special metadata if needed.
